10:50.804 --> 10:54.431
This sums up America's
relationship with North Korea.

10:54.441 --> 10:57.534
Each sees the other as an
unrelenting adversary,

10:57.544 --> 10:59.903
since both countries have limited access

10:59.913 --> 11:01.739
to the other's point of view.

11:01.749 --> 11:02.906
The bottom line is

11:02.916 --> 11:04.808
North Korea's got to
change its behavior.

11:04.818 --> 11:08.278
And as the West's hard-lined
rhetoric ramped up,

11:08.288 --> 11:09.846
throughout the night, we could see

11:09.856 --> 11:12.449
the mass mobilization
of military vehicles,

11:12.459 --> 11:15.017
preparing for their
annual show of force.

11:15.027 --> 11:18.722
The Day of the Sun celebration
commemorates the birthday

11:18.732 --> 11:22.459
of North Korea's eternal
president, Kim Il-sung.

11:22.469 --> 11:24.394
It also gives them the opportunity

11:24.404 --> 11:27.029
to broadcast their
strength over the airwaves

11:27.039 --> 11:30.499
with a public military parade.

11:55.967 --> 11:58.126
So, I'm having a complete
sensory overload.

11:58.136 --> 12:00.561
I don't know whether to laugh or cry

12:00.571 --> 12:02.772
or be scared or entertained.

12:27.965 --> 12:30.458
Like Stalin's Soviet marches,

12:30.468 --> 12:32.793
the parade was a jaw-dropping display

12:32.803 --> 12:35.704
of highly choreographed military might.

12:37.241 --> 12:40.367
And much like those May
Day parades of the past,

12:40.377 --> 12:44.471
this show of force was
aimed directly at the US

12:44.481 --> 12:47.049
_

12:47.256 --> 12:50.948
_

12:51.813 --> 12:55.568
_

12:56.334 --> 12:59.052
_

13:01.269 --> 13:03.886
_

13:04.842 --> 13:06.975
_

13:18.647 --> 13:21.440
I believe we're watching
the first display

13:21.450 --> 13:23.809
of North Korea's first-ever ICBMs

13:23.819 --> 13:26.052
that are capable of reaching America.

13:31.394 --> 13:34.453
As the senior politician
just claimed in his speech,

13:34.463 --> 13:36.355
they will launch if provoked.

13:36.365 --> 13:39.557
The North's claims to
have this capability

13:39.567 --> 13:41.459
are disputed by experts.

13:41.469 --> 13:44.596
But there is no doubting
the nationalist fervor

13:44.606 --> 13:47.565
that unveiling missiles helps incite.

13:55.617 --> 13:58.943
The parade kicked off
a dramatic escalation.

13:58.953 --> 14:02.013
The following day,
the North conducted a failed,

14:02.023 --> 14:04.115
though very real, missile test.

14:04.125 --> 14:06.183
... following North
Korea's show of force,

14:06.193 --> 14:08.019
failing in spectacular fashion.

14:08.029 --> 14:10.187
Then, US Vice President Mike Pence

14:10.197 --> 14:13.057
made a surprise visit to
the demilitarized zone

14:13.067 --> 14:15.026
between North and South Korea.

14:15.036 --> 14:17.461
We stand with the people of South Korea,

14:17.471 --> 14:20.364
um, and all options are on the table.

14:20.374 --> 14:21.698
And since then,

14:21.708 --> 14:23.867
amidst increasingly bellicose rhetoric

14:23.877 --> 14:26.003
on President Trump's Twitter feed,

14:26.013 --> 14:28.539
yet more missile tests.

14:28.549 --> 14:32.208
While the Western media was quick
to pounce on their launch failures,

14:32.218 --> 14:34.277
only a short time later,

14:34.287 --> 14:36.179
they successfully tested a missile

14:36.189 --> 14:38.757
that experts believe
could strike the US.

14:40.126 --> 14:42.085
Concrete proof that their technology

14:42.095 --> 14:44.154
is years ahead of expectations,

14:44.164 --> 14:46.056
has triggered an even stronger reaction

14:46.066 --> 14:47.590
from the Trump administration.

14:47.600 --> 14:49.659
As far as North Korea is concerned,

14:49.669 --> 14:51.527
I have some pretty severe things

14:51.537 --> 14:52.963
that we're thinking about.

14:52.973 --> 14:54.897
Make no mistake,

14:54.907 --> 14:57.667
North Korea's launch of an ICBM

14:57.677 --> 15:01.370
is a clear and sharp
military escalation.

15:01.380 --> 15:03.439
We had witnessed firsthand

15:03.449 --> 15:06.742
how echo chambers,
without direct dialogue,

15:06.752 --> 15:09.679
can help beat the drum to war.

15:09.689 --> 15:11.681
We will defeat any attack,

15:11.691 --> 15:13.516
and we will meet any use

15:13.526 --> 15:15.651
of conventional or nuclear weapons

15:15.661 --> 15:18.420
with an overwhelming
and effective response.

15:18.430 --> 15:20.255
The question now

15:20.265 --> 15:22.958
is how far are both sides willing to go

15:22.968 --> 15:24.493
before a war of words

15:24.503 --> 15:26.761
becomes something much more dangerous?

15:36.748 --> 15:40.274
By most definitions,
Somalia is a failed state.

15:40.284 --> 15:43.077
It's been ravaged by famine, civil war,

15:43.087 --> 15:45.013
and become a base for piracy.

15:45.023 --> 15:47.716
Most recently,
it's seen horrendous violence

15:47.726 --> 15:49.884
by the terrorist group Al-Shabaab.

15:49.894 --> 15:52.620
More than two million Somalis have fled

15:52.630 --> 15:53.954
because of those factors,

15:53.964 --> 15:57.191
including 150,000 who came to the US.

15:57.201 --> 15:59.460
But today, many of these émigrés

15:59.470 --> 16:01.162
are starting to return to Somalia

16:01.172 --> 16:03.531
to try to fix their country for good.

16:08.619 --> 16:10.971
Somalia hasn't had a
functioning government

16:10.981 --> 16:12.606
in more than 25 years.

16:12.616 --> 16:15.009
They've been plagued by
decades of civil war

16:15.019 --> 16:16.443
and widespread terrorism.

16:16.453 --> 16:19.747
Billions of dollars of international
support hasn't worked.

16:19.757 --> 16:22.982
But today, there's a new source of hope:

16:22.992 --> 16:24.751
the Somali diaspora.

16:24.761 --> 16:27.054
Thousands of Somali
Westerners are returning.

16:27.064 --> 16:30.657
Unlike foreigners, they have an
inherent commitment to this country,

16:30.667 --> 16:33.293
and their Western education
and work experience

16:33.303 --> 16:35.562
is unparalleled in the region.

16:35.572 --> 16:37.497
We traveled to Southern Somalia,

16:37.507 --> 16:39.799
devastated by severe drought,

16:39.809 --> 16:41.968
where Somali-Canadian doctor, Hodan Ali,

16:41.978 --> 16:44.871
is overseeing a medical
assessment and aid delivery.

16:44.881 --> 16:47.840
We have a shipment brought by UNICEF,

16:47.850 --> 16:49.976
and they have brought supplies

16:49.986 --> 16:52.946
to deal with the acute outbreak

16:52.956 --> 16:54.614
of watery diarrhea.

16:54.624 --> 16:57.649
Because the town is completely
surrounded by Al-Shabaab,

16:57.659 --> 16:59.693
all aid has to be flown in.

17:01.930 --> 17:04.823
This is the community treatment center

17:04.833 --> 17:07.726
for, um, acute watery diarrhea,

17:07.736 --> 17:10.865
one of two facilities
in the entire region.

17:10.906 --> 17:12.335
_

17:12.483 --> 17:14.351
_

17:14.541 --> 17:16.237
_

17:16.679 --> 17:19.031
_

17:19.041 --> 17:20.347
_

17:20.667 --> 17:21.723
_

17:22.584 --> 17:24.609
We left Somalia pre-civil war.

17:24.619 --> 17:26.377
I have been blessed and privileged

17:26.387 --> 17:28.346
to have lived the life that I've lived,

17:28.356 --> 17:30.515
because we're talking about a society

17:30.525 --> 17:32.383
that has not had formal education,

17:32.393 --> 17:34.719
formal institutions, for over 25 years.

17:34.729 --> 17:38.189
We have generations that
have seen nothing but war.

17:38.199 --> 17:40.024
What we need now is investment,

17:40.034 --> 17:41.826
human investment, human resources,

17:41.836 --> 17:45.730
because we cannot depend on
international interventions.

17:45.740 --> 17:47.197
Who... who is going to do it,

17:47.207 --> 17:49.634
if people like myself don't do it?

17:49.644 --> 17:51.135
Somalia's still a dangerous place.

17:51.145 --> 17:54.204
There were several explosions
just in the last few days.

17:54.214 --> 17:57.041
Why leave a comfortable,
safe life in Canada?

17:57.051 --> 17:59.510
Somalia is definitely a dangerous place,

17:59.520 --> 18:01.911
but I don't look at the danger.

18:01.921 --> 18:04.080
I look at the potential and the need

18:04.090 --> 18:05.649
that the country has.

18:07.060 --> 18:09.286
After filming for just over an hour,

18:09.296 --> 18:11.655
local Intel came in that Al-Shabaab,

18:11.665 --> 18:14.291
known for targeting and
executing Westerners,

18:14.301 --> 18:15.624
wasn't far away.

18:15.635 --> 18:17.694
Apparently Al-Shabaab got
word that we're here,

18:17.704 --> 18:19.328
and that aid just came into the town,

18:19.338 --> 18:21.064
so we got to get out of here.

18:24.301 --> 18:26.736
While Dr. Hodan's work in
the most desperate parts

18:26.746 --> 18:28.337
of Somalia has been crucial,

18:28.347 --> 18:29.973
back in Mogadishu,

18:29.983 --> 18:32.709
she's attempting to build
Somalia's health care system

18:32.719 --> 18:34.343
from the ground up.

18:34.353 --> 18:39.081
Dr. Hodan just opened this
beautiful health center.

18:39.091 --> 18:40.957
It's definitely an upgrade.

18:42.295 --> 18:44.053
The facility really is a facility

18:44.063 --> 18:46.955
for first... um, primary care services.

18:46.965 --> 18:48.257
Preventative care,

18:48.267 --> 18:50.293
chronic illnesses like
diabetes, hypertension,

18:50.303 --> 18:52.494
which is really,
really on the rise here.

18:52.504 --> 18:55.463
See, this bed here is a maternity bed,

18:55.473 --> 18:59.201
but if you go to your
average clinic or hospital,

18:59.211 --> 19:01.003
women don't have this type of bed.

19:01.013 --> 19:03.405
The number one killer of Somali women

19:03.415 --> 19:05.407
is postpartum hemorrhage.

19:05.417 --> 19:07.275
A woman is about to go into labor,

19:07.285 --> 19:09.257
they pray for her, for her return.

19:09.268 --> 19:11.595
Because they know that's the
deadliest thing she could do.

19:11.606 --> 19:12.814
Absolutely.

19:12.824 --> 19:15.183
Now we're gonna go upstairs.

19:15.193 --> 19:18.687
We have our quick
inpatient facility here

19:18.697 --> 19:21.889
for folks who need
immediate rehydration.

19:21.899 --> 19:24.291
Every room has a sink,

19:24.301 --> 19:27.061
and we will be putting antiseptic soaps

19:27.071 --> 19:30.664
and all the means to make sure that
people are cleaning their hands.

19:30.674 --> 19:32.867
So, that seems pretty standard.

19:32.877 --> 19:34.736
- You know, basic sanitation.
- Yes.

19:34.746 --> 19:37.404
- How rare is it here?
- Very rare.

19:37.414 --> 19:40.374
People who have come here have said,
"You know, this is different."

19:40.384 --> 19:42.610
And that's the idea.
It needs to be different.

19:42.620 --> 19:45.946
Not different that it is crazy,
out-of-this-world.

19:45.956 --> 19:49.149
It's just basic services
that I would be providing

19:49.159 --> 19:51.652
in... in Hamilton, Ontario, right?

19:51.662 --> 19:53.420
Because at the end of the day,

19:53.430 --> 19:57.423
it's... it's a place
that anything you do...

19:57.433 --> 19:59.592
makes a difference.

19:59.602 --> 20:02.629
But for a country with a
bloody history, like Somalia,

20:02.639 --> 20:04.798
the first pillar to
restoring the country

20:04.808 --> 20:06.800
is providing security.

20:06.810 --> 20:08.568
We joined the Somali National Army

20:08.578 --> 20:10.837
and AMISOM, the African
peacekeeping force,

20:10.847 --> 20:13.373
widely credited with
stabilizing the country,

20:13.383 --> 20:15.937
as they visited a
recently opened school.

20:19.422 --> 20:21.381
Twenty-five years of anarchy,

20:21.391 --> 20:24.150
we're not going to have
it solved overnight,

20:24.160 --> 20:26.252
but with our partners from Africa,

20:26.262 --> 20:27.987
the AMISOM, we've tried our best,

20:27.997 --> 20:29.522
and I think you can see the results.

20:29.532 --> 20:31.390
Did you live in the UK? Yes.

20:31.400 --> 20:33.725
I hear that accent.
You're a diaspora, huh?

20:33.735 --> 20:36.195
- Yes.
- Wow. Why did you return?

20:36.205 --> 20:37.830
To serve my country.

20:40.642 --> 20:42.134
Before AMISOM took over

20:42.144 --> 20:45.104
for the dysfunctional Somali
National Army in 2007,

20:45.114 --> 20:47.506
Al-Shabaab controlled most of Mogadishu

20:47.516 --> 20:48.973
and much of the country.

20:48.983 --> 20:51.075
Today, they're much weaker

20:51.085 --> 20:52.952
and rely on one-off attacks.

20:54.122 --> 20:56.648
During the Battle of Mogadishu in 2011,

20:56.658 --> 20:58.784
AMISOM and the SNA
fought with Al-Shabaab

20:58.794 --> 21:01.653
for control over a significant
national landmark,

21:01.663 --> 21:04.488
the Mogadishu football stadium.

21:04.498 --> 21:06.490
So, Al-Shabaab used to control

21:06.500 --> 21:08.326
this whole stadium, this whole area,

21:08.336 --> 21:11.196
and it was a big win for AMISOM

21:11.206 --> 21:12.504
when they took it back.

