21:28.489 --> 21:30.147
The UPDF were also, at the time,

21:30.157 --> 21:31.549
at a placed called Uruba.

21:31.559 --> 21:32.583
That's the Uruba Hotel.

21:32.593 --> 21:35.720
So, you now control all
of this and way beyond?

21:35.730 --> 21:37.354
We are beyond this.

21:37.364 --> 21:39.522
If Somalia was a no-go zone,

21:39.532 --> 21:41.391
uh, a few years back,

21:41.401 --> 21:43.526
today it's open, it's a normal country,

21:43.536 --> 21:45.262
and slowly we are progressing.

21:45.272 --> 21:46.463
The last ten years

21:46.473 --> 21:50.133
have been years of
progress for this country.

21:50.143 --> 21:51.631
The businesses and construction

21:51.642 --> 21:52.902
popping up throughout the city

21:52.912 --> 21:55.772
were encouraging signs of
the country rebuilding.

21:55.782 --> 21:58.975
One very busy, unexpected
storefront caught our eye.

21:58.985 --> 22:01.244
This street here is regularly bombed,

22:01.254 --> 22:03.813
but it turns out there
is a juice shop open.

22:03.823 --> 22:07.069
This is some of the most extreme
gentrification I've ever seen.

22:07.080 --> 22:08.752
- Welcome.
- I like your sunglasses.

22:08.763 --> 22:11.106
- All right. Thank you.
- You guys got good vibes in here.

22:11.117 --> 22:12.746
Where I came from, the US,

22:12.785 --> 22:15.191
where this kind of shop
actually was very popular.

22:15.201 --> 22:17.360
Maybe I should try something like that,

22:17.370 --> 22:19.495
and immediately it became a hit.

22:19.505 --> 22:21.797
About 300 or 400 customers

22:21.807 --> 22:23.532
visit this store every day.

22:23.542 --> 22:24.767
- Wow.
- Yeah.

22:24.777 --> 22:27.603
We know there's electronic
shops that actually do good.

22:27.613 --> 22:29.237
There's a lot of travel agencies.

22:29.247 --> 22:32.374
There's also a fashion shop
here called "Cadaani."

22:32.384 --> 22:33.876
They want change, and that's actually

22:33.886 --> 22:36.144
what we want to try to show
off to Mogadishu people,

22:36.154 --> 22:38.346
that this is also a relatively safe city

22:38.356 --> 22:41.316
where you can do business.

22:41.326 --> 22:44.452
"Safety" is still a relative
term here in Mogadishu,

22:44.462 --> 22:45.820
but the returning diaspora

22:45.830 --> 22:47.989
that is fueling much of
the economic growth here

22:47.999 --> 22:50.458
are determined to succeed.

22:50.468 --> 22:52.860
Like Ahmed Jama,
who returned from the UK

22:52.870 --> 22:54.529
to open the Village Restaurant,

22:54.539 --> 22:57.098
a popular spot among Somali Westerners.

