Okay. Congratulations.

26:34.386 --> 26:35.786
Can I ask, are you a diaspora?

26:35.797 --> 26:37.316
_

26:37.327 --> 26:39.219
- The United States?
- I lived in Washington.

26:39.230 --> 26:40.814
Eighty percent of the ministers

26:40.824 --> 26:42.650
appointed here are diaspora

26:42.660 --> 26:44.952
and their presence is
giving people hope.

26:44.962 --> 26:46.720
But this shift toward Westernization

26:46.731 --> 26:49.533
triggered Al-Shabaab's string
of attacks soon after.

26:50.668 --> 26:52.726
About an hour after we
left Villa Somalia,

26:52.736 --> 26:54.695
a bomb exploded at the front gates,

26:54.705 --> 26:56.063
killing several people,

26:56.073 --> 26:58.732
and many more went off in the
capital while we were there.

26:58.742 --> 27:01.301
In what was meant to be an
attack against Al-Shabaab,

27:01.311 --> 27:04.705
one of the ministers we met,
Abas Abdullahi Sheikh,

27:04.715 --> 27:06.906
was shot and killed by security forces

27:06.916 --> 27:08.708
shortly after we left the country.

27:08.718 --> 27:10.310
But despite these attacks,

27:10.320 --> 27:13.046
the diaspora have become
a formidable force

27:13.056 --> 27:16.216
pushing back against extremism.

27:16.226 --> 27:17.850
Part of what has fueled Al-Shabaab,

27:17.860 --> 27:20.487
which translates to
"the youth" in Arabic,

27:20.497 --> 27:23.489
is their ability to win the
hearts and minds of young people.

27:23.499 --> 27:25.124
Elman Peace and Human Rights Centre

27:25.134 --> 27:28.427
is an organization that
rehabilitates radicalized children,

27:28.437 --> 27:30.930
aiming to end the cycle of violence.

27:30.941 --> 27:32.281
